## 1. PREAMBLE

The ZEQ Framework / HULYAS Math is an open-source, non-von Neumann state machine architecture grounded in the physical discovery of the HulyaPulse and the Zeqond. This technology is released to humanity as "Open Science" to serve as a universal infrastructure for truth, data integrity, and physical resonance.

This license is designed to ensure that while the mathematics and code are free to use, the fundamental discoveries are permanently recognized and never diluted by corporate co-opting or rebranding.

## 2. THE DEFINED CONSTANTS

For the purposes of this license and all derivative works:

The HulyaPulse is defined as the fundamental resonance frequency of 1.287 Hz.

The Zeqond is defined as the discrete temporal state-lock interval of 0.777 seconds.

The HULYAS Math is the mathematical framework used to phase-lock computation to these constants.

